14
00:00:54,340 --> 00:00:56,260
 They still taught the class? 

15
00:00:56,260 --> 00:00:57,400
 Yes. 

16
00:00:57,400 --> 00:01:01,420
I contacted Lee Si Wu since he didn't come to the class today.

17
00:01:01,420 --> 00:01:03,330
Are you sure it was only Lee Si Wu?

18
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:05,390
Kids from other academies could've gone.

19
00:01:05,390 --> 00:01:06,670
He was alone, apparently.

20
00:01:06,670 --> 00:01:10,980
It was supposed to be two hours, but it got longer.

21
00:01:12,770 --> 00:01:16,800
He skipped my class but stayed at that class until the end?

22
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,860
I'll ask him for details during the class next week.

23
00:01:22,610 --> 00:01:24,700
I'd like to hear it soon.

24
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,710
About what they talked about.

25
00:01:26,710 --> 00:01:29,200
 Episode 5 

26
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,560
- I'll go now.
 - Thank you.

27
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:38,760
- Take care. 
 - See you.
 - Bye.

28
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:51,970
We still need to talk more, right?

29
00:01:51,970 --> 00:01:54,510
I got so dizzy that I thought I'd die.

30
00:01:54,510 --> 00:01:56,370
Let's walk a bit.

31
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:03,910
Well, why don't you help me here if you're free?

32
00:02:03,910 --> 00:02:05,620
Hold on.

33
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:08,110
I'm thinking about another man right now.

34
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:11,140
Who? Mr. Lee Jun Ho?

35
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:13,260
Isn't he kind of strange?

36
00:02:13,260 --> 00:02:15,360
What do you mean? How?

37
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:19,640
To be specific, when he's around, Seo Hye Jin...

38
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,140
She's kind of weird.

39
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:23,030
What do you mean?

40
00:02:23,830 --> 00:02:28,200
Strangely, it feels like I'm seeing the old Seo Hye Jin.

41
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:32,070
That could happen.

42
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:36,200
Your old habits come out when you see friends from elementary school.

43
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:41,000
Like how you talk like a soldier when you see your old military buddies.

44
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,520
I never joined the military.

45
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,870
It's just an example. An example.

46
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:48,870
Men tend to be like that.

47
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:50,610
Is that it?

48
00:03:00,490 --> 00:03:02,190
Aren't you cold?

49
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:04,550
No, I'm okay.

50
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,890
What are you thinking about?

51
00:03:14,570 --> 00:03:16,200
Si Wu.

52
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:19,610
Me, too.

53
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,890
Will he remember us positively?

54
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:27,100
He'd never be able to forget.

55
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,790
How do you know?

56
00:03:28,790 --> 00:03:31,070
I'm the living proof.

57
00:03:31,070 --> 00:03:33,490
I've never forgotten.

58
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:38,760
But it's kind of unfair.

59
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,580
What do you mean?

60
00:03:40,580 --> 00:03:45,790
The lecture today was about twice as good as my first class.

61
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:51,750
Because Mr. Lee Jun Ho taught half of today's class.

62
00:03:53,930 --> 00:03:56,360
Didn't you get flustered?

63
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:59,150
We used less than half of the material we prepared.

64
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,850
Not at all.

65
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:03,820
But I wondered what you thought at that moment.

66
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:06,810
You don't have to tell me if it's hard to explain.

67
00:04:13,910 --> 00:04:16,390
It's because my mind went blank.

68
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:21,910
The prepared material...

69
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:25,440
Maybe it should've been something other than the perfect score strategy.

70
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:28,290
That's what I thought at first.

71
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:31,770
I somehow ended up standing in front of the blackboard,

72
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:36,470
and I completely forgot what I had prepared with you at that moment.

73
00:04:36,470 --> 00:04:41,640
The perfect score strategy, stuff like score-improving tips, and everything.

74
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:45,360
So, I thought I should enjoy the piece together.

75
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,700
It reminded me of the first class I taught you.

76
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:50,400
I think it felt similar to that.

77
00:04:51,590 --> 00:04:54,560
Of course, Si Wu isn't as stupid as you were.

78
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,720
Geez.

79
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,660
I wasn't stupid.

80
00:04:58,660 --> 00:05:01,760
I was a genius who differed from others from the beginning.

81
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:09,130
The academy will give me a disadvantage somehow.

82
00:05:09,130 --> 00:05:11,190
You should keep a distance from me for now.

83
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:14,300
It's okay if it looks like we had a falling out because of today.

84
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:16,430
Don't come to work tomorrow.

85
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,500
What if I don't want to do that?

86
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,740
Huh?

87
00:05:21,740 --> 00:05:25,150
"I'll take care of the rest. You go forward."

88
00:05:25,150 --> 00:05:28,580
It seems you want to say something cool like that.

89
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,610
But you can't.

90
00:05:31,610 --> 00:05:33,490
I'm okay.

91
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:37,170
I've experienced it even though it was long ago.

92
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:40,150
The academy can't readily bug me about it either.

93
00:05:40,150 --> 00:05:46,540
To make more money quicker than the section chief, deputy, and team leader above me,

94
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:48,800
I quit my corporate job and came here.

95
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:53,470
I wouldn't have come here if I was going to hide behind my boss to save myself.

96
00:05:54,440 --> 00:06:01,180
You and I prepared this project together as teachers and we'll take equal responsibility. And...

97
00:06:02,330 --> 00:06:06,680
well, I got what I wanted.

98
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:10,470
Yes, the man in power seemed angry.

99
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:13,410
Gosh.

100
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:16,690
It's a pity everyone knows we failed,

101
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:21,610
but I'm satisfied my debut was noisy.

102
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:25,530
There are two exams each semester. We'll continue to get chances.

103
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:29,680
Just hold onto Chanyeong High tightly.

104
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:32,880
I'll bring us Huiwon High.

105
00:06:37,110 --> 00:06:41,050
 YG Science Academy 

106
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:45,820
 Huiwon High School 

107
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,070
 Good morning. 

108
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:56,040
 Final Exam Briefing - Chanyeong High 10th Grade 

109
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,890
 I set aside the supplementary academy class material for you. 

110
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:59,820
 Pick it up this evening. 

111
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:02,120
 Tell me about yesterday, too. 

112
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:10,410
Everyone who signed up for the briefing came. It's a full house.

113
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:15,980
Switch the presentation to the one on the USB stick on the laptop.

114
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:18,460
I displayed the file you checked last.

115
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:20,390
I checked multiple times.

116
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:23,770
You said Seo Hye Jin and Lee Jun Ho gave a lecture to Si Wu.

117
00:07:23,770 --> 00:07:26,570
My teaching method was too conventional.

118
00:07:26,570 --> 00:07:28,090
So I prepared something.

119
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:31,210
 Final Exam Briefing - Chanyeong High 10th Grade 

120
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:35,310
 Daechi Choeseon Korean Briefing for Parents 

121
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:52,530
 Chanyeong High 10th Grade 2nd Semester 
 Description of Final Exam 

122
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:02,430
I'm Director Choi Hyeong Seon of Choeseon Korean.

123
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:06,290
It's nice to meet the Chanyeong High parents for the first time.

124
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:11,650
I'll get started immediately.

125
00:08:11,650 --> 00:08:13,690
 'I'm excited!' 

126
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:17,370
You must all remember.

127
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:22,400
It caused a redo in the last midterm exam.

128
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:27,490
Let me ask you one thing.

129
00:08:27,490 --> 00:08:31,590
What's the most important exam for the children?

130
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:37,530
The first-semester midterm in the 10th grade when school starts grading?

131
00:08:37,530 --> 00:08:40,550
The 11th-grade exams that the transcripts focus on a lot?

132
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:43,610
Or the college entrance exam?

133
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:46,840
They're all wrong.

134
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,790
The answer is...

135
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:50,780
 "This exam" 

136
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:54,800
The school's exam trend changes every year.

137
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:58,610
Will you panic every time without knowing how to respond

138
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:01,390
and barge into the school every time?

139
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:05,450
Complaining to the teachers who are holding the transcripts?

140
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:07,860
While the offending teacher

141
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:12,340
causes major chaos by changing the exam rules?

142
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:15,070
The students

143
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:20,790
are much weaker than you think.

144
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:23,240
Just because they're familiar with the old teacher,

145
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:25,080
the schedule is more convenient,

146
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:28,440
they'll want to give up. Don't let that happen.

147
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:35,130
You need to control them until they get accepted to a college.

148
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:42,270
The Gray Witch must've started the briefing.

149
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:46,030
You must be very disappointed about the event yesterday.

150
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:47,610
I'm sorry.

151
00:09:47,610 --> 00:09:51,480
Not at all. You're the ones who must feel hurt.

152
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:55,840
It would've been nice if you heard Mr. Lee's lecture.

153
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,600
He's stronger in the actual battles.

154
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:00,380
You gave a lecture?

155
00:10:00,380 --> 00:10:03,060
Because even one student matters.

156
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:06,390
Good job.

157
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:10,890
Hard work like that makes the academy's image.

158
00:10:12,230 --> 00:10:14,660
You're making me feel even worse.

159
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:18,640
No, no. I thought you might be tormented thinking that.

160
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,980
That's why I called you early in the morning.

161
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:24,220
I thought it'd be better to see you earlier.

162
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:28,880
We didn't meet the goal with Huiwon High, but Chanyeong High—

163
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:34,720
I noticed something very unexpected in you this time.

164
00:10:35,850 --> 00:10:40,020
Your selfless attitude in training Mr. Lee properly.

165
00:10:40,020 --> 00:10:43,260
A sense of drive with no fear of a counter-attack.

166
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:47,740
Wow, I didn't know you had that kind of ability.

167
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:53,950
And on top of that you gave an entire lecture for just one student?

168
00:10:53,950 --> 00:10:55,790
Wow.

169
00:10:55,790 --> 00:11:01,550
What an exemplary attitude that'll inspire newer teachers.

170
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:04,340
- That's— 
- Team Leader Seo,

171
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:08,760
you shouldn't be stuck in a small classroom.

172
00:11:10,020 --> 00:11:13,310
Chanyeong High 11th grade?

173
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,360
I thought you'd like it.

174
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:20,030
But I requested 10th grade.

175
00:11:20,030 --> 00:11:24,540
I didn't ask to split Team Leader Seo's class. I wanted to get my own students—

176
00:11:24,540 --> 00:11:27,680
So you don't want it?

177
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:30,480
Well, more than not wanting to—

178
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:34,170
How many 11th-grade Chanyeong High students do we currently have?

179
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:36,900
A little more than 80.

180
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,840
- I don't know the exact number— 
- I see.

181
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:43,080
You'll have about 40 students if you split a class with Mr. Lee.

182
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:45,370
Mr. Lee, too?

183
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:49,140
Why? Do you want all 80 students?

184
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:51,520
No, it's not that.

185
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:55,850
Or are you disappointed since they'll be in 12th grade soon?

186
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:58,380
Since they'll be leaving soon?

187
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:03,120
No.

188
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:07,590
I think it's a good thing. The new teachers rarely get to teach 12th grade.

189
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:13,240
Not everyone gets to start in Daechi-dong

190
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:15,490
with an opportunity like this.

191
00:12:15,490 --> 00:12:18,900
Yes. Of course, I know that.

192
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:24,200
Please feel pressured that the academy is highly looking forward to you two.

193
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,650
Okay.

194
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:31,070
Team Leader Seo will help you a lot.

195
00:12:32,070 --> 00:12:37,170
I never stopped thinking the Korean department is

196
00:12:37,170 --> 00:12:41,070
the core of our academy.

197
00:12:41,070 --> 00:12:42,950
We have more departments now

198
00:12:42,950 --> 00:12:46,780
since we took over Assistant Director Wu Seung Hui's Victory Academy.

199
00:12:46,780 --> 00:12:50,660
But I always thought the Korean department

200
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:53,400
would maintain the tradition of our academy.

201
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:58,300
Thinking now, I put a lot of effort into the Korean department.

202
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:01,030
Starting with advertising,

203
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:03,390
I've always been supportive of the Korean teachers.

204
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:07,460
Thanks to that, Ms. Seo settled down at a young age, too.

205
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:09,110
I'm grateful for that.

206
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:10,810
Yes.

207
00:13:10,810 --> 00:13:13,310
But I always try

208
00:13:13,310 --> 00:13:17,920
to be objective and critical.

209
00:13:19,260 --> 00:13:21,080
"Am I

210
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:25,490
a proper leader as the director of the academy?

211
00:13:26,290 --> 00:13:29,090
Am I getting lazy

212
00:13:29,090 --> 00:13:32,870
by wanting to make a steady profit?"

213
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:39,970
After criticizing myself harshly,

214
00:13:39,970 --> 00:13:43,400
I reached a conclusion.

215
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,810
Now is the time for growth in quality,

216
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:50,440
not quantity.

217
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,080
And one more thing.

218
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:57,430
I've been forgetting that Team Leader Seo is key to that growth.

219
00:13:57,430 --> 00:13:59,790
I've been reflecting on that.

220
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,000
That means...

221
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,530
Since you're a top-class lecturer,

222
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:07,350
you need to broaden your horizons now.

223
00:14:08,070 --> 00:14:11,280
Ms. Seo, take it easy and work for

224
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:14,520
the Gangbuk branch opening task force.

225
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:45,820
Do you understand this situation?

226
00:14:45,820 --> 00:14:47,440
No.

227
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:08,010
What did he mean? What task force all of a sudden?

228
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:12,320
There's no such thing. There's no team, either.

229
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:15,950
The Assistant Director will want to see you soon. Let me keep it brief.

230
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:17,860
Why would she want to see me?

231
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:21,560
She'll give you part of my class.

232
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:24,980
I think it'll be Chanyeong High—probably 11th grade.

233
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:26,160
What do you mean—

234
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:30,340
Since we don't know how many of the 10th-grade Choeseon Korean will take.

235
00:15:30,340 --> 00:15:32,520
I know, but why would I be taking your students?

236
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:35,680
To make me leave empty-handed.

237
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:38,160
Just because that one free lecture failed?

238
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:42,750
No, they've probably been looking for a chance.

239
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:47,010
A lecturer like me is a double-edged sword for an academy.

240
00:15:47,010 --> 00:15:48,680
I make them a good profit,

241
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:52,610
but the academy would suffer a lot if I left with my students.

242
00:15:52,610 --> 00:15:57,160
That's why they've been trying to split up my students.

243
00:15:58,140 --> 00:16:01,180
"Demotions often get presented as an honor."

244
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:05,460
I like how quickly you understand.

245
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:10,200
So, that means you're...

246
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:14,910
You're screwed because of me, right?

247
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,300
Excuse me.

248
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:22,340
 Assistant Director Wu Seung Hui 

249
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:24,650
Answer it.

250
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:53,240
You said you just hung out after the academy class on the weekend.

251
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:56,540
We did. After finishing the homework.

252
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:58,470
You traitors.

253
00:17:00,940 --> 00:17:03,020
I'm so busy. Who is it?

254
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,600
"Mom."

255
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:09,410
Hey, Mom.

256
00:17:09,410 --> 00:17:13,070
It's break time, of course. Isn't that why you called?

257
00:17:15,270 --> 00:17:17,070
Yes.

258
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:19,440
Was the briefing fun?

259
00:17:21,370 --> 00:17:22,770
What?

260
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:26,280
Don't do that, Mom.

261
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:28,760
Don't do that field study thing.

262
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,280
